# üìò Python Data Types

Python has several built-in data types categorized into:

## ‚úÖ Numeric Types
| Type     | Description                  | Example           |
|----------|------------------------------|-------------------|
| int      | Integer (whole number)       | `x = 10`          |
| float    | Decimal number               | `y = 3.14`        |
| complex  | Complex number               | `z = 2 + 3j`      |

## ‚úÖ Sequence Types
| Type     | Description                  | Example                    |
|----------|------------------------------|----------------------------|
| str      | String (text)                | `name = "Drashti"`         |
| list     | Ordered, mutable collection  | `fruits = ["apple", "banana"]` |
| tuple    | Ordered, immutable collection| `colors = ("red", "green")` |
| range    | Sequence of numbers          | `nums = range(5)`          |

## ‚úÖ Mapping Type
| Type     | Description        | Example                         |
|----------|--------------------|---------------------------------|
| dict     | Key-value mapping  | `person = {"name": "Aarav"}`    |

## ‚úÖ Set Types
| Type       | Description          | Example              |
|------------|----------------------|----------------------|
| set        | Unique, unordered    | `s = {1, 2, 3}`      |
| frozenset  | Immutable set        | `fs = frozenset([4, 5, 6])` |

## ‚úÖ Binary Types
| Type        | Description              | Example                    |
|-------------|--------------------------|----------------------------|
| bytes       | Immutable binary data    | `b = b"hello"`             |
| bytearray   | Mutable binary data      | `ba = bytearray(5)`        |
| memoryview  | View on binary data      | `mv = memoryview(b"abc")`  |

## ‚úÖ Special Type
| Type       | Description              | Example     |
|------------|--------------------------|-------------|
| NoneType   | Represents null value    | `x = None`  |

---

### üîç Check Data Type
```python
x = 10
print(type(x))  # Output: <class 'int'>


Example: memoryview
data = bytearray(b"abc")
mv = memoryview(data)
print(mv[0])     # 97 (ASCII of 'a')
mv[0] = 65       # Change 'a' to 'A'
print(data)      # bytearray(b'Abc')
